#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:179
msgid "Argument scalarization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:181
msgid ""
"When you write a kernel that takes `&[f32]`, the host and device don't agree "
"on how to represent a Rust slice in memory -- the struct layout can differ "
"between the host's x86 ABI and the NVPTX ABI. cuda-oxide solves this by "
"**scalarizing** aggregate types at the kernel boundary: decomposing them "
"into primitive values that both sides interpret identically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:171
