#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:383
msgid "Unified memory and HMM"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:385
msgid ""
"By default, GPUs operate in a **separate address space** from the CPU. A GPU "
"cannot dereference an ordinary host pointer -- the address simply doesn't "
"map to anything in the GPU's page tables. The traditional CUDA workflow "
"therefore requires explicit allocation in device memory followed by explicit "
"copies:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:390
msgid ""
"┌──────────────────┐              ┌──────────────────┐\n"
"│   CPU Memory     │    PCIe /    │   GPU Memory     │\n"
"│   (host DRAM)    │◄────────────►│   (device HBM)   │\n"
"│                  │   NVLink     │                  │\n"
"└──────────────────┘    copy      └──────────────────┘\n"
"   Separate address spaces -- GPU cannot dereference host pointers\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/memory-and-data-movement.md:399
msgid ""
"CUDA provides mechanisms that relax this restriction by letting the GPU "
"access host memory transparently, at the cost of page-fault latency on first "
"access."
msgstr ""

